sec-aggregate-error-constructor.name: AggregateError
sec-aggregate-error-constructor.summary: The AggregateError() constructor creates an error for several errors that need to be wrapped in a single error.
sec-aggregate-error-constructor.title: AggregateError() constructor

sec-aggregate-error-objects.name: AggregateError
sec-aggregate-error-objects.summary: The AggregateError object represents an error when several errors need to be wrapped in a single error. It is thrown when multiple errors need to be reported by an operation, for example by Promise.any(), when all promises passed to it reject.
sec-aggregate-error-objects.title: AggregateError

sec-array-constructor.name: Array
sec-array-constructor.summary: The Array() constructor is used to create Array objects.
sec-array-constructor.title: Array() constructor

sec-array.prototype.at.name: at
sec-array.prototype.at.summary: The at() method takes an integer value and returns the item at that index, allowing for positive and negative integers. Negative integers count back from the last item in the array.
sec-array.prototype.at.title: Array.prototype.at()

sec-array.prototype.concat.name: concat
sec-array.prototype.concat.summary: The concat() method is used to merge two or more arrays. This method does not change the existing arrays, but instead returns a new array.
sec-array.prototype.concat.title: Array.prototype.concat()

sec-array.prototype.copywithin.name: copyWithin
sec-array.prototype.copywithin.summary: The copyWithin() method shallow copies part of an array to another location in the same array and returns it without modifying its length.
sec-array.prototype.copywithin.title: Array.prototype.copyWithin()

sec-array.prototype.entries.name: entries
sec-array.prototype.entries.summary: The entries() method returns a new Array Iterator object that contains the key/value pairs for each index in the array.
sec-array.prototype.entries.title: Array.prototype.entries()

sec-array.prototype.every.name: every
sec-array.prototype.every.summary: The every() method tests whether all elements in the array pass the test implemented by the provided function. It returns a Boolean value.
sec-array.prototype.every.title: Array.prototype.every()

sec-array.prototype.fill.name: fill
sec-array.prototype.fill.summary: The fill() method changes all elements in an array to a static value, from a start index (default 0) to an end index (default array.length). It returns the modified array.
sec-array.prototype.fill.title: Array.prototype.fill()

sec-array.prototype.filter.name: filter
sec-array.prototype.filter.summary: The filter() method creates a shallow copy of a portion of a given array, filtered down to just the elements from the given array that pass the test implemented by the provided function.
sec-array.prototype.filter.title: Array.prototype.filter()

sec-array.prototype.find.name: find
sec-array.prototype.find.summary: The find() method returns the first element in the provided array that satisfies the provided testing function. If no values satisfy the testing function, undefined is returned.
sec-array.prototype.find.title: Array.prototype.find()

sec-array.prototype.findindex.name: findIndex
sec-array.prototype.findindex.summary: The findIndex() method returns the index of the first element in an array that satisfies the provided testing function. If no elements satisfy the testing function, -1 is returned.
sec-array.prototype.findindex.title: Array.prototype.findIndex()

sec-array.prototype.findlast.name: findLast
sec-array.prototype.findlast.summary: The findLast() method iterates the array in reverse order and returns the value of the first element that satisfies the provided testing function. If no elements satisfy the testing function, undefined is returned.
sec-array.prototype.findlast.title: Array.prototype.findLast()

sec-array.prototype.findlastindex.name: findLastIndex
sec-array.prototype.findlastindex.summary: The findLastIndex() method iterates the array in reverse order and returns the index of the first element that satisfies the provided testing function. If no elements satisfy the testing function, -1 is returned.
sec-array.prototype.findlastindex.title: Array.prototype.findLastIndex()

sec-array.prototype.flat.name: flat
sec-array.prototype.flat.summary: The flat() method creates a new array with all sub-array elements concatenated into it recursively up to the specified depth.
sec-array.prototype.flat.title: Array.prototype.flat()

sec-array.prototype.flatmap.name: flatMap
sec-array.prototype.flatmap.summary: The flatMap() method returns a new array formed by applying a given callback function to each element of the array, and then flattening the result by one level. It is identical to a map() followed by a flat() of depth 1 (arr.map(...args).flat()), but slightly more efficient than calling those two methods separately.
sec-array.prototype.flatmap.title: Array.prototype.flatMap()

sec-array.prototype.foreach.name: forEach
sec-array.prototype.foreach.summary: The forEach() method executes a provided function once for each array element.
sec-array.prototype.foreach.title: Array.prototype.forEach()

sec-array.from.name: from
sec-array.from.summary: The Array.from() static method creates a new, shallow-copied Array instance from an iterable or array-like object.
sec-array.from.title: Array.from()

sec-array.prototype.includes.name: includes
sec-array.prototype.includes.summary: The includes() method determines whether an array includes a certain value among its entries, returning true or false as appropriate.
sec-array.prototype.includes.title: Array.prototype.includes()

sec-array.prototype.indexof.name: indexOf
sec-array.prototype.indexof.summary: The indexOf() method returns the first index at which a given element can be found in the array, or -1 if it is not present.
sec-array.prototype.indexof.title: Array.prototype.indexOf()

sec-array.isarray.name: isArray
sec-array.isarray.summary: The Array.isArray() static method determines whether the passed value is an Array.
sec-array.isarray.title: Array.isArray()

sec-array.prototype.join.name: join
sec-array.prototype.join.summary: The join() method creates and returns a new string by concatenating all of the elements in an array (or an array-like object), separated by commas or a specified separator string. If the array has only one item, then that item will be returned without using the separator.
sec-array.prototype.join.title: Array.prototype.join()

sec-array.prototype.keys.name: keys
sec-array.prototype.keys.summary: The keys() method returns a new Array Iterator object that contains the keys for each index in the array.
sec-array.prototype.keys.title: Array.prototype.keys()

sec-array.prototype.lastindexof.name: lastIndexOf
sec-array.prototype.lastindexof.summary: The lastIndexOf() method returns the last index at which a given element can be found in the array, or -1 if it is not present. The array is searched backwards, starting at fromIndex.
sec-array.prototype.lastindexof.title: Array.prototype.lastIndexOf()

sec-properties-of-array-instances-length.name: length
sec-properties-of-array-instances-length.summary: The length property of an object which is an instance of type Array sets or returns the number of elements in that array. The value is an unsigned, 32-bit integer that is always numerically greater than the highest index in the array.
sec-properties-of-array-instances-length.title: Array.prototype.length

sec-array.prototype.map.name: map
sec-array.prototype.map.summary: The map() method creates a new array populated with the results of calling a provided function on every element in the calling array.
sec-array.prototype.map.title: Array.prototype.map()

sec-array.of.name: of
sec-array.of.summary: The Array.of() method creates a new Array instance from a variable number of arguments, regardless of number or type of the arguments.
sec-array.of.title: Array.of()

sec-array.prototype.pop.name: pop
sec-array.prototype.pop.summary: The pop() method removes the last element from an array and returns that element. This method changes the length of the array.
sec-array.prototype.pop.title: Array.prototype.pop()

sec-array.prototype.push.name: push
sec-array.prototype.push.summary: The push() method adds one or more elements to the end of an array and returns the new length of the array.
sec-array.prototype.push.title: Array.prototype.push()

sec-array.prototype.reduce.name: reduce
sec-array.prototype.reduce.summary: The reduce() method executes a user-supplied "reducer" callback function on each element of the array, in order, passing in the return value from the calculation on the preceding element. The final result of running the reducer across all elements of the array is a single value.
sec-array.prototype.reduce.title: Array.prototype.reduce()

sec-array.prototype.reduceright.name: reduceRight
sec-array.prototype.reduceright.summary: The reduceRight() method applies a function against an accumulator and each value of the array (from right-to-left) to reduce it to a single value.
sec-array.prototype.reduceright.title: Array.prototype.reduceRight()

sec-array.prototype.reverse.name: reverse
sec-array.prototype.reverse.summary: The reverse() method reverses an array in place and returns the reference to the same array, the first array element now becoming the last, and the last array element becoming the first. In other words, elements order in the array will be turned towards the direction opposite to that previously stated.
sec-array.prototype.reverse.title: Array.prototype.reverse()

sec-array.prototype.shift.name: shift
sec-array.prototype.shift.summary: The shift() method removes the first element from an array and returns that removed element. This method changes the length of the array.
sec-array.prototype.shift.title: Array.prototype.shift()

sec-array.prototype.slice.name: slice
sec-array.prototype.slice.summary: The slice() method returns a shallow copy of a portion of an array into a new array object selected from start to end (end not included) where start and end represent the index of items in that array. The original array will not be modified.
sec-array.prototype.slice.title: Array.prototype.slice()

sec-array.prototype.some.name: some
sec-array.prototype.some.summary: The some() method tests whether at least one element in the array passes the test implemented by the provided function. It returns true if, in the array, it finds an element for which the provided function returns true; otherwise it returns false. It doesn't modify the array.
sec-array.prototype.some.title: Array.prototype.some()

sec-array.prototype.sort.name: sort
sec-array.prototype.sort.summary: The sort() method sorts the elements of an array in place and returns the reference to the same array, now sorted. The default sort order is ascending, built upon converting the elements into strings, then comparing their sequences of UTF-16 code units values.
sec-array.prototype.sort.title: Array.prototype.sort()

sec-array.prototype.splice.name: splice
sec-array.prototype.splice.summary: The splice() method changes the contents of an array by removing or replacing existing elements and/or adding new elements in place. To access part of an array without modifying it, see slice().

ie.notes: From Internet Explorer 5.5 through 8, all elements of the array will not be deleted if deleteCount is omitted. This behavior was fixed in Internet Explorer 9.

sec-array.prototype.splice.title: Array.prototype.splice()

sec-array.prototype.tolocalestring.name: toLocaleString
sec-array.prototype.tolocalestring.summary: The toLocaleString() method returns a string representing the elements of the array. The elements are converted to Strings using their toLocaleString methods and these Strings are separated by a locale-specific String (such as a comma ",").
sec-array.prototype.tolocalestring.title: Array.prototype.toLocaleString()

sec-array.prototype.tostring.name: toString
sec-array.prototype.tostring.summary: The toString() method returns a string representing the specified array and its elements.
sec-array.prototype.tostring.title: Array.prototype.toString()

sec-array.prototype.unshift.name: unshift
sec-array.prototype.unshift.summary: The unshift() method adds one or more elements to the beginning of an array and returns the new length of the array.
sec-array.prototype.unshift.title: Array.prototype.unshift()

sec-array.prototype.values.name: values
sec-array.prototype.values.summary: The values() method returns a new array iterator object that iterates the value of each index in the array.

nodejs.notes: The --harmony-array-prototype-values flag is required; the --harmony flag is not sufficient in this case.

sec-array.prototype.values.title: Array.prototype.values()

sec-array.prototype-@@iterator.name: @@iterator
sec-array.prototype-@@iterator.summary: The @@iterator method of an Array object implements the iterable protocol and allows arrays to be consumed by most syntaxes expecting iterables, such as the spread syntax and for...of loops. It returns an iterator that yields the value of each index in the array.

firefox.notes: A placeholder property named @@iterator is used.
A placeholder property named iterator is used.

sec-array.prototype-@@iterator.title: Array.prototype[@@iterator]()

sec-get-array-@@species.name: @@species
sec-get-array-@@species.summary: The Array[@@species] accessor property returns the constructor used to construct return values from array methods.
sec-get-array-@@species.title: get Array[@@species]

sec-array.prototype-@@unscopables.name: @@unscopables
sec-array.prototype-@@unscopables.summary: The @@unscopables data property contains property names that were not included in the ECMAScript standard prior to the ES2015 version and that are ignored for with statement-binding purposes.
sec-array.prototype-@@unscopables.title: Array.prototype[@@unscopables]

sec-array-objects.name: Array
sec-array-objects.summary: The Array object, as with arrays in other programming languages, enables storing a collection of multiple items under a single variable name, and has members for performing common array operations.
sec-array-objects.title: Array

sec-arraybuffer-constructor.name: ArrayBuffer
sec-arraybuffer-constructor.summary: The ArrayBuffer() constructor is used to create ArrayBuffer objects.
sec-arraybuffer-constructor.title: ArrayBuffer() constructor

sec-get-arraybuffer.prototype.bytelength.name: byteLength
sec-get-arraybuffer.prototype.bytelength.summary: The byteLength accessor property represents the length of an ArrayBuffer in bytes.
sec-get-arraybuffer.prototype.bytelength.title: ArrayBuffer.prototype.byteLength

sec-arraybuffer.isview.name: isView
sec-arraybuffer.isview.summary: The ArrayBuffer.isView() method determines whether the passed value is one of the ArrayBuffer views, such as typed array objects or a DataView.
sec-arraybuffer.isview.title: ArrayBuffer.isView()

sec-arraybuffer.prototype.slice.name: slice
sec-arraybuffer.prototype.slice.summary: The slice() method returns a new ArrayBuffer whose contents are a copy of this ArrayBuffer's bytes from begin, inclusive, up to end, exclusive.

firefox.notes: The non-standard ArrayBuffer.slice() method has been removed in Firefox 53 (but the standardized version ArrayBuffer.prototype.slice() is kept.

sec-arraybuffer.prototype.slice.title: ArrayBuffer.prototype.slice()

sec-get-arraybuffer-@@species.name: @@species
sec-get-arraybuffer-@@species.summary: The ArrayBuffer[@@species] accessor property returns the constructor used to construct return values from array buffer methods.
sec-get-arraybuffer-@@species.title: get ArrayBuffer[@@species]

sec-arraybuffer-objects.name: ArrayBuffer
sec-arraybuffer-objects.summary: The ArrayBuffer object is used to represent a generic, fixed-length raw binary data buffer.
sec-arraybuffer-objects.title: ArrayBuffer

sec-async-function-objects.name: AsyncFunction
sec-async-function-objects.summary: The AsyncFunction constructor creates a new async function object. In JavaScript, every asynchronous function is actually an AsyncFunction object.
sec-async-function-objects.title: AsyncFunction

sec-asyncgenerator-prototype-next.name: next
sec-asyncgenerator-prototype-next.summary: The next() method returns the next value in the sequence.
sec-asyncgenerator-prototype-next.title: AsyncGenerator.prototype.next()

sec-asyncgenerator-prototype-return.name: return
sec-asyncgenerator-prototype-return.summary: The return() method of an async generator acts as if a return statement is inserted in the generator's body at the current suspended position, which finishes the generator and allows the generator to perform any cleanup tasks when combined with a try...finally block.
sec-asyncgenerator-prototype-return.title: AsyncGenerator.prototype.return()

sec-asyncgenerator-prototype-throw.name: throw
sec-asyncgenerator-prototype-throw.summary: The throw() method of an async generator acts as if a throw statement is inserted in the generator's body at the current suspended position, which informs the generator of an error condition and allows it to handle the error, or perform cleanup and close itself.
sec-asyncgenerator-prototype-throw.title: AsyncGenerator.prototype.throw()

sec-asyncgenerator-objects.name: AsyncGenerator
sec-asyncgenerator-objects.summary: The AsyncGenerator object is returned by an async generator function and it conforms to both the async iterable protocol and the async iterator protocol.
sec-asyncgenerator-objects.title: AsyncGenerator

sec-asyncgeneratorfunction-objects.name: AsyncGeneratorFunction
sec-asyncgeneratorfunction-objects.summary: The AsyncGeneratorFunction constructor creates a new async generator function object. In JavaScript, every async generator function is actually an AsyncGeneratorFunction object.
sec-asyncgeneratorfunction-objects.title: AsyncGeneratorFunction

sec-atomics.add.name: add
sec-atomics.add.summary: The static Atomics.add() method adds a given value at a given position in the array and returns the old value at that position. This atomic operation guarantees that no other write happens until the modified value is written back.
sec-atomics.add.title: Atomics.add()

sec-atomics.and.name: and
sec-atomics.and.summary: The static Atomics.and() method computes a bitwise AND with a given value at a given position in the array, and returns the old value at that position. This atomic operation guarantees that no other write happens until the modified value is written back.
sec-atomics.and.title: Atomics.and()

sec-atomics.compareexchange.name: compareExchange
sec-atomics.compareexchange.summary: The static Atomics.compareExchange() method exchanges a given replacement value at a given position in the array, if a given expected value equals the old value. It returns the old value at that position whether it was equal to the expected value or not. This atomic operation guarantees that no other write happens until the modified value is written back.
sec-atomics.compareexchange.title: Atomics.compareExchange()

sec-atomics.exchange.name: exchange
sec-atomics.exchange.summary: The static Atomics.exchange() method stores a given value at a given position in the array and returns the old value at that position. This atomic operation guarantees that no other write happens between the read of the old value and the write of the new value.
sec-atomics.exchange.title: Atomics.exchange()

sec-atomics.islockfree.name: isLockFree
sec-atomics.islockfree.summary: The static Atomics.isLockFree() method is used to determine whether the Atomics methods use locks or atomic hardware operations when applied to typed arrays with the given element byte size. It returns false if the given size is not one of the BYTES_PER_ELEMENT property of integer TypedArray types.
sec-atomics.islockfree.title: Atomics.isLockFree()

sec-atomics.load.name: load
sec-atomics.load.summary: The static Atomics.load() method returns a value at a given position in the array.
sec-atomics.load.title: Atomics.load()

sec-atomics.notify.name: notify
sec-atomics.notify.summary: The static Atomics.notify() method notifies up some agents that are sleeping in the wait queue.
sec-atomics.notify.title: Atomics.notify()

sec-atomics.or.name: or
sec-atomics.or.summary: The static Atomics.or() method computes a bitwise OR with a given value at a given position in the array, and returns the old value at that position. This atomic operation guarantees that no other write happens until the modified value is written back.
sec-atomics.or.title: Atomics.or()

sec-atomics.store.name: store
sec-atomics.store.summary: The static Atomics.store() method stores a given value at the given position in the array and returns that value.
sec-atomics.store.title: Atomics.store()

sec-atomics.sub.name: sub
sec-atomics.sub.summary: The static Atomics.sub() method subtracts a given value at a given position in the array and returns the old value at that position. This atomic operation guarantees that no other write happens until the modified value is written back.
sec-atomics.sub.title: Atomics.sub()

sec-atomics.wait.name: wait
sec-atomics.wait.summary: The static Atomics.wait() method verifies that a given position in an Int32Array still contains a given value and if so sleeps, awaiting a wakeup or a timeout. It returns a string which is either "ok", "not-equal", or "timed-out".
sec-atomics.wait.title: Atomics.wait()

sec-atomics.xor.name: xor
sec-atomics.xor.summary: The static Atomics.xor() method computes a bitwise XOR with a given value at a given position in the array, and returns the old value at that position. This atomic operation guarantees that no other write happens until the modified value is written back.
sec-atomics.xor.title: Atomics.xor()

sec-atomics-object.name: Atomics
sec-atomics-object.summary: The Atomics object provides atomic operations as static methods. They are used with SharedArrayBuffer and ArrayBuffer objects.
sec-atomics-object.title: Atomics

sec-bigint-constructor.name: BigInt
sec-bigint-constructor.summary: The BigInt() function returns a value of type bigint.
sec-bigint-constructor.title: BigInt() constructor

sec-bigint.asintn.name: asIntN
sec-bigint.asintn.summary: The BigInt.asIntN static method clamps a BigInt value to the given number of bits, and returns that value as a signed integer.
sec-bigint.asintn.title: BigInt.asIntN()

sec-bigint.asuintn.name: asUintN
sec-bigint.asuintn.summary: The BigInt.asUintN static method clamps a BigInt value to the given number of bits, and returns that value as an unsigned integer.
sec-bigint.asuintn.title: BigInt.asUintN()

sec-bigint.prototype.tostring.name: toString
sec-bigint.prototype.tostring.summary: The toString() method returns a string representing the specified BigInt value. The trailing "n" is not part of the string.
sec-bigint.prototype.tostring.title: BigInt.prototype.toString()

sec-bigint.prototype.valueof.name: valueOf
sec-bigint.prototype.valueof.summary: The valueOf() method returns the wrapped primitive value of a BigInt object.
sec-bigint.prototype.valueof.title: BigInt.prototype.valueOf()

sec-bigint-objects.name: BigInt
sec-bigint-objects.summary: BigInt is a primitive wrapper object used to represent and manipulate primitive bigint values  which are too large to be represented by the number primitive.
sec-bigint-objects.title: BigInt

sec-typedarray-constructors.name: BigInt64Array
sec-typedarray-constructors.summary: The BigInt64Array() typed array constructor creates a new BigInt64Array object, which is, an array of 64-bit signed integers in the platform byte order. If control over byte order is needed, use DataView instead. The contents are initialized to 0n. Once established, you can reference elements in the array using the object's methods, or by using standard array index syntax (that is, using bracket notation).
sec-typedarray-constructors.title: BigInt64Array() constructor

sec-typedarray-constructors.name: BigUint64Array
sec-typedarray-constructors.summary: The BigUint64Array() typed array constructor creates a new BigUint64Array object, which is, an array of 64-bit unsigned integers in the platform byte order. If control over byte order is needed, use DataView instead. The contents are initialized to 0n. Once established, you can reference elements in the array using the object's methods, or by using standard array index syntax (that is, using bracket notation).
sec-typedarray-constructors.title: BigUint64Array() constructor

sec-typedarray-constructors.name: Float32Array
sec-typedarray-constructors.summary: The Float32Array() typed array constructor creates a new Float32Array object, which is, an array of 32-bit floating point numbers (corresponding to the C float data type) in the platform byte order. If control over byte order is needed, use DataView instead. The contents are initialized to 0. Once established, you can reference elements in the array using the object's methods, or using standard array index syntax (that is, using bracket notation).
sec-typedarray-constructors.title: Float32Array() constructor

sec-typedarray-constructors.name: Float64Array
sec-typedarray-constructors.summary: The Float64Array() typed array constructor creates a new Float64Array object, which is, an array of 64-bit floating point numbers (corresponding to the C double data type) in the platform byte order. If control over byte order is needed, use DataView instead. The contents are initialized to 0. Once established, you can reference elements in the array using the object's methods, or using standard array index syntax (that is, using bracket notation).
sec-typedarray-constructors.title: Float64Array() constructor

sec-typedarray-constructors.name: Int16Array
sec-typedarray-constructors.summary: The Int16Array() typed array constructor creates an array of twos-complement 16-bit signed integers in the platform byte order. If control over byte order is needed, use DataView instead. The contents are initialized to 0. Once established, you can reference elements in the array using the object's methods, or using standard array index syntax (that is, using bracket notation).
sec-typedarray-constructors.title: Int16Array() constructor

sec-typedarray-constructors.name: Int32Array
sec-typedarray-constructors.summary: The Int32Array() typed array constructor creates an array of twos-complement 32-bit signed integers in the platform byte order. If control over byte order is needed, use DataView instead. The contents are initialized to 0. Once established, you can reference elements in the array using the object's methods, or using standard array index syntax (that is, using bracket notation).
sec-typedarray-constructors.title: Int32Array() constructor

sec-typedarray-constructors.name: Int8Array
sec-typedarray-constructors.summary: The Int8Array() constructor creates a typed array of twos-complement 8-bit signed integers. The contents are initialized to 0. Once established, you can reference elements in the array using the object's methods, or using standard array index syntax (that is, using bracket notation).
sec-typedarray-constructors.title: Int8Array() constructor

sec-typedarray-constructors.name: Uint16Array
sec-typedarray-constructors.summary: The Uint16Array() typed array constructor creates an array of 16-bit unsigned integers in the platform byte order.
sec-typedarray-constructors.title: Uint16Array() constructor

sec-typedarray-constructors.name: Uint32Array
sec-typedarray-constructors.summary: The Uint32Array() typed array constructor creates an array of 32-bit unsigned integers in the platform byte order. If control over byte order is needed, use DataView instead. The contents are initialized to 0. Once established, you can reference elements in the array using the object's methods, or using standard array index syntax (that is, using bracket notation).
sec-typedarray-constructors.title: Uint32Array() constructor

sec-typedarray-constructors.name: Uint8Array
sec-typedarray-constructors.summary: The Uint8Array() constructor creates a typed array of 8-bit unsigned integers. The contents are initialized to 0. Once established, you can reference elements in the array using the object's methods, or using standard array index syntax (that is, using bracket notation).
sec-typedarray-constructors.title: Uint8Array() constructor

sec-typedarray-constructors.name: Uint8ClampedArray
sec-typedarray-constructors.summary: The Uint8ClampedArray() constructor creates a typed array of 8-bit unsigned integers clamped to 0-255; if you specified a value that is out of the range of [0,255], 0 or 255 will be set instead; if you specify a non-integer, the nearest integer will be set. The contents are initialized to 0. Once established, you can reference elements in the array using the object's methods, or using standard array index syntax (that is, using bracket notation).
sec-typedarray-constructors.title: Uint8ClampedArray() constructor

sec-typedarray-objects.name: BigInt64Array
sec-typedarray-objects.summary: The BigInt64Array typed array represents an array of 64-bit signed integers in the platform byte order. If control over byte order is needed, use DataView instead. The contents are initialized to 0n. Once established, you can reference elements in the array using the object's methods, or by using standard array index syntax (that is, using bracket notation).
sec-typedarray-objects.title: BigInt64Array

sec-typedarray-objects.name: BigUint64Array
sec-typedarray-objects.summary: The BigUint64Array typed array represents an array of 64-bit unsigned integers in the platform byte order. If control over byte order is needed, use DataView instead. The contents are initialized to 0n. Once established, you can reference elements in the array using the object's methods, or by using standard array index syntax (that is, using bracket notation).
sec-typedarray-objects.title: BigUint64Array

sec-typedarray-objects.name: TypedArray
sec-typedarray-objects.summary: A TypedArray object describes an array-like view of an underlying binary data buffer. There is no global property named TypedArray, nor is there a directly visible TypedArray constructor. Instead, there are a number of different global properties, whose values are typed array constructors for specific element types, listed below. On the following pages you will find common properties and methods that can be used with any typed array containing elements of any type.
sec-typedarray-objects.title: TypedArray

sec-boolean-constructor.name: Boolean
sec-boolean-constructor.summary: The Boolean() constructor can create Boolean objects or return primitive values of type boolean.
sec-boolean-constructor.title: Boolean() constructor

sec-boolean.prototype.tostring.name: toString
sec-boolean.prototype.tostring.summary: The toString() method returns a string representing the specified boolean value.
sec-boolean.prototype.tostring.title: Boolean.prototype.toString()

sec-boolean.prototype.valueof.name: valueOf
sec-boolean.prototype.valueof.summary: The valueOf() method returns the primitive value of a Boolean object.
sec-boolean.prototype.valueof.title: Boolean.prototype.valueOf()

sec-boolean-objects.name: Boolean
sec-boolean-objects.summary: The Boolean object represents a truth value: true or false.
sec-boolean-objects.title: Boolean

sec-dataview-constructor.name: DataView
sec-dataview-constructor.summary: The DataView() constructor is used to create DataView objects.

sec-function-constructor.name: Function
sec-function-constructor.summary: The Function() constructor creates a new Function object. Calling the constructor directly can create functions dynamically, but suffers from security and similar (but far less significant) performance issues as eval().
